-- London Stock Exchange Agrees to Merge With Toronto Bourse; Rolet to Be CEO
-- B y   D a v i d   M e r r i t t
-- 2011-02-09T07:10:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-09/london-stock-exchange-agrees-to-merge-with-toronto-bourse-rolet-to-be-ceo.html
  London Stock Exchange Group Plc , the
210-year-old bourse operator, agreed to buy Toronto Stock
Exchange owner  TMX Group Inc . in an all-share transaction as the
companies cut costs to counter lost market share.  LSE Chief Executive Officer  Xavier Rolet  will be CEO of the
enlarged group, the companies said today in a Regulatory News
Service statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Merritt at 
 dmerritt1@bloomberg.net  